El Al, Knafaim Rise on Leasing Unit’s Jet Purchase Agreement

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-08-14T15:23:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/el-al-shareholder-knafaim-gain-on-global-leasing-plane-purchase.html
El Al Israel Airlines (ELAL)  Ltd., the
country’s national carrier, and controlling shareholder  Knafaim
Holdings Ltd. (KNFM)  advanced after Knafaim said its aircraft leasing
unit agreed to buy three jets.  El Al gained 3.6 percent, its biggest jump since March 16,
to 0.773 shekel at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Knafaim,
which owns 39 percent of El Al and all of Global Knafaim Leasing
Ltd., closed 3.8 percent higher at 20.58 shekels.  Global Knafaim Leasing agreed to buy two Airbus SAS A320
jets and one Boeing Co. 737-800 airplane for an estimated $80
million, Knafaim Holdings said in a statement to the Tel Aviv
stock exchange today.  Knafaim expects the unit to generate $173 million in the
next four years from leasing after the acquisitions are
completed, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
